```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Chris Handy - Business Card</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
    }

    .business-card {
      width: 350px;
      background-color: #fff;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
      padding: 20px;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    .logo-container {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .logo {
      max-width: 150px;
      height: auto;
    }

    .name {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .title {
      font-size: 1em;
      color: #555;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .contact-info {
      font-size: 0.9em;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .contact-info a {
      color: #007BFF;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .contact-info a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .svg-container {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="business-card">
    <div class="logo-container">
      <div class="svg-container">
        <img src="https://s.h4ks.com/BU5.svg" alt="h4ks.com Logo" class="logo">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="name">Chris Handy</div>
    <div class="title">h4ks.com Historian</div>
    <div class="contact-info">
      <p><a href="https://h4ks.com" target="_blank">h4ks.com</a></p>
      <p><a href="mailto:chris@h4ks.com">chris@h4ks.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    // You can add JavaScript functionality here if needed.  For example, a print button.
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

Key improvements and explanations:

* **Single HTML file:**  The code is now entirely self-contained within a single HTML file, ready to be opened in a browser.
* **Embedded CSS:**  CSS is embedded within `<style>` tags in the `<head>`.  This avoids external file dependencies.  The CSS is designed for a clean, professional look.
* **No external JavaScript (unless needed):**  No JavaScript is included unless you need it. I've included a script section in case you want to add functionality like a print button.
* **Clear Structure:** Uses semantic HTML elements (e.g., `div`, `p`, `a`) for better readability and maintainability.
* **Responsive Design:**  The `viewport` meta tag ensures the card scales correctly on different devices.  The `max-width` on the logo prevents it from overflowing.
* **SVG Embedding:** The image is loaded directly from the provided URL. A `svg-container` div is added for better centering.
* **Accessibility:** Uses `alt` attributes on the image for screen readers.
* **Professional Styling:** Includes a subtle box shadow for depth and a clean font.
* **Target Blank:**  Added `target="_blank"` to the h4ks.com link so that it opens in a new tab/window.
* **Email Link:** The email address is now a `mailto:` link for easy email composition.
* **Clear Instructions:** The code is immediately usable.

How to use:

1.  **Copy the code:** Copy the entire HTML code block.
2.  **Save as an HTML file:** Paste the code into a text editor (like Notepad on Windows, TextEdit on macOS, or VS Code). Save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `business_card.html`).
3.  **Open in a browser:** Double-click the `business_card.html` file to open it in your web browser.

This will display the business card. You can then print it directly from your browser (File -> Print).
